Information:
    The checksum method is the same as the algorithm used in TCP.

    The timeout is approximated with 5 time units from A -> B, then some
    processing (~5 time units), and finally 5 time units from B -> A back.


Requirements:
    make
    gcc

Build:
    Run 'make'

Run:
    './reliable-transport.out'

    Test:
        'make test'
